The paper discusses reinforcement learning in robotics, which is a subfield of robotics (cs.RO). The focus on reward functions and state-initialization suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The mention of viability kernels and failure suggests a connection to control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the use of vision-based tasks in the experiments suggests a connection to computer vision (cs.CV).
